Children stayed home from school on 3 September 2019, following violent protests in the Joburg city centre overnight. Violence and looting erupted in the Joburg CBD. Several shops and cars were set alight. A night vigil was held at UCT on 2 September 2019 for murdered student Uyinene Mrwetyana. Currie Cup preparations for the Golden Lions on 3 September 2019. SABC CEO Madoda Mxakwe at the State Capture Commission on 3 September 2019.